  "body": "The object store has the capability to sync to another object store in the same cluster or another cluster in a different geographical region. See the [Ceph docs](http://docs.ceph.com/docs/master/radosgw/multisite/). Rook needs to enhance the object store CRDs to enable this scenario to seamlessly replicate between object stores.\r\n\r\nRook currently creates a realm, zone group, zone, and new pools for each new object store. Each of those has the same name as the object store, and the pools include the name of the object store. In this way, Rook can easily support multiple, independent object stores.\r\n\r\nAs a proof of concept, we can use the Rook toolbox to execute the commands needed to set up the multi-site replication. From there, we can design what it should look like with CRDs.\r\n",
